article.headline: North Texas 72, Denver 67
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Shawnson Johnson had 19 points and 13 rebounds as North Texas fought off a second-half rally to beat Denver 72-67 Thursday night. North Texas (6-8, 1-1 Sun Belt) led 46-26 at halftime. Denver (8-6, 0-2) opened the second half with a 12-0 run and later scored nine unanswered points to take a 1-point lead with just more than eight minutes remaining in the game. The Mean Green regained the lead 62-61 with 4:13 remaining and outscored Denver 10-6 in the game's final minutes to extend their lead. Calvin Watson added 11 points for North Texas and Jerome Rogers had 10. Erik Benzel scored 17 points and Carvell McAlister added 16 for Denver.
